feed.title: Inverleigh Nature Conservation Reserve
feed.subtitle: a.k.a. as Inverleigh Flora & Fauna Reserve. 1050ha of remnant grassy woodland, 30km west of Geelong.

entry.title: Chiloglottis spp.
entry.content: I was told this is a natural hybrid between C. trapeziformis and C valida. It was growing in a colony near the little fenced-off area in the reserve.

entry.title: Sherardia arvensis
entry.content: Four petal lilac flowers are very small.

entry.title: Chrysocephalum spp.
entry.content: A single bud on the end of each stem.

entry.title: Thysanotus patersonii
entry.content: The small mauve to violet flowers , about 1cm wide, are born singly at the end of short branches on the flowering stem.
